description*.en: In aerospace engineering, mass ratio is a measure of the efficiency of a rocket. It describes how much more massive the vehicle is with propellant than without; that is, it is the ratio of the rocket's wet mass (vehicle plus contents plus propellant) to its dry mass (vehicle plus contents)

title: MassRatio
description: In aerospace engineering, mass ratio is a measure of the efficiency of a rocket.
